{"ID":270298, "Text":"<div class=\"page\"><div class=\"pageNum\"><a name=\"298\"><\/a><div class=\"prev\"><a href=\"stpjs297.html\">Prev<\/a><\/div><div class=\"next\"><a href=\"stpjs299.html\">Next<\/a><\/div>\n\t\t\t    STPJS 298<\/div>\n  <p class=\"cont\">may destroy<span class=\"footRef\">1<\/span>&mdash;any person that he can find that will yield to him, he will bind him,<span class=\"footRef\">2<\/span> and take\n  possession of the body<span class=\"footRef\">3<\/span> and reign there, glorying in it mightily, not caring that he had got merely\n  a stolen body; and by and by some one having authority will come along and cast him out<span class=\"footRef\">4<\/span> and\n  restore the tabernacle to its rightful owner.<span class=\"footRef\">5<\/span> The devil steals a tabernacle because he has not one of\n  his own: but if he steals one, he is always liable to be turned out of doors.<\/p>\n  <div class=\"topic \">Calling and Election<\/div>\n  <p class=\"std\">Now, there is some grand secret<span class=\"footRef\">6<\/span> here, and keys to unlock the subject. Notwithstanding the\n  apostle exhorts them to add to their faith, virtue, knowledge, temperance,<span class=\"footRef\">7<\/span> etc., yet he exhorts them\n  to make their calling and election sure.<span class=\"footRef\">8<\/span> And though they had heard an audible voice from heaven\n  bearing testimony that Jesus was the Son of God,<span class=\"footRef\">9<\/span> yet he says we have a more sure word of\n  prophecy, whereunto ye do well that ye take heed as unto a light shining in a dark place.<span class=\"footRef\">10<\/span> Now,\n  wherein could they have a more sure word of prophecy than to hear the voice of God saying, This\n  is my beloved Son.<span class=\"footRef\">11<\/span><\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">Now for the secret and grand key. Though they might hear the voice of God and know that Jesus\n  was the Son of God, this would be no evidence that their election and calling was made sure, that\n  they had part with Christ,<span class=\"footRef\">12<\/span> and were joint heirs with Him.<span class=\"footRef\">13<\/span> They then would want that more sure\n  word of prophecy,<span class=\"footRef\">14<\/span> that they were sealed in the heavens<span class=\"footRef\">15<\/span> and had the promise of eternal life in the\n  kingdom of God.<span class=\"footRef\">16<\/span> Then, having this promise sealed<span class=\"footRef\">17<\/span> unto them, it was an anchor to the soul, sure\n  and steadfast.<span class=\"footRef\">18<\/span> Though the thunders might roll and lightnings flash, and earthquakes bellow, and\n  war gather thick around, yet this hope and knowledge would support the soul in every hour of trial,\n  trouble and tribulation.<span class=\"footRef\">19<\/span> Then knowledge through our Lord and Savior Jesus Christ<span class=\"footRef\">20<\/span> is the grand\n  key that unlocks the glories and mysteries of the kingdom<span class=\"footRef\">21<\/span> of heaven.<\/p>\n  <p class=\"std\">Compare this principle once with Christendom at the present day, and where are they, with all\n  their boasted religion, piety and sacredness while at the same time they are crying out against\n  prophets, apostles, angels, revelations, prophesying and visions, etc. Why, they are just ripening for\n  the damnation<span class=\"footRef\">22<\/span> of hell.<span class=\"footRef\">23<\/span> They will be damned, for they reject the most glorious principles of the\n  Gospel of Jesus Christ<span class=\"footRef\">24<\/span> and treat with disdain<\/p>\n  <div class=\"footnotes\">\n    <div class=\"footnote\">1. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112477\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112477)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112477)\">Hel. 8:28<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"113196\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 113196)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(113196)\">D&amp;C 10:27<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116448\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116448)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116448)\">D&amp;C 132:57<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">2. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"111204\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 111204)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(111204)\">2 Ne. 9:45<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">3. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"112272\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 112272)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(112272)\">Alma 40:13<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">4. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107917\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107917)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107917)\">Matt. 9:33<\/a><\/span>;\n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"108339\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 108339)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(108339)\">Mark 7:26-30<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">5. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"107991\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 107991)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(107991)\">Matt. 12:43-45<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">6. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"116133\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 116133)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(116133)\">D&amp;C 128:11<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">7. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110505\"><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"sx(this, 110505)\">&nbsp;<\/a><a href=\"javascript:void(0)\" onclick=\"gs(110505)\">2 Pet. 1:5-8<\/a><\/span>\n    <\/div>\n    <div class=\"footnote\">8. \n      <span class=\"citation\" id=\"110511\"><a hre